<h2>Rapid Descriptions</h2>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView56' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid6165">Powerhouse Inflow</a></b> (Class N/A, Mile -0.4)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Pit#1 Powerhouse</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaPhotoDetailView95' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/879893/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/879893.jpg">
</a>
<i>Pit#1 Powerhouse</i></div><div>Photo by Paul Martzen taken 10/02/11 @ 850 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>The powerhouse typically releases high flows during the day, year round.&nbsp; At night the powerhouse shuts off, leaving a base flow in the river of around 500 cfs.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView57' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101807">Put In Lagoon</a></b> (Class N/A)<br>
<p>There is a boat ramp in the day use area at the downstream end of the campground. &nbsp; The ramp accomodates trailers unloading rafts and drift boats for fishing float trips. &nbsp;</p><p>The ramp is in a small protected lagoon.&nbsp; From the lagoon, boaters float past a small fishing area and out into the lower half of campground rapid.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView58' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101802">Campground Rapid</a></b> (Class I, Mile 0.1)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Morning Mist</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaPhotoDetailView99' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/879892/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/879892.jpg">
</a>
<i>Morning Mist</i></div><div>Photo by Paul Martzen taken 10/02/11 @ 850 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>The put in is below the steepest half of this rapid, but the lower half is still a nice drop with fun waves. &nbsp;</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView59' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101786">Lions Club</a></b> (Class I, Mile 0.3)<br>
<p>A Lions Club Picnic area is hidden in the trees on river right at the start of this rapid. &nbsp; A small spring also enters the river from the picnic area.&nbsp; The rapid is long and straight with the biggest drop at the very end.&nbsp; A distinct basalt cliff looms over the end where the river turns left.</p><p>Boaters could take out or put in at the picnic area, since there is road access close to the river.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView60' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101787">Spring confluence</a></b> (Class II, Mile 0.5)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Spring Rapid</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaPhotoDetailView103' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/879884/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/879884.jpg">
</a>
<i>Spring Rapid</i></div><div>Photo by Paul Martzen taken 10/02/11 @ 850 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>Water from a spring enters the river on the right at the bottom of Lion's Club rapid, just before a basalt cliff.&nbsp; It is easy to miss the spring from the river, but you can hike down to it from the campground.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView61' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101803">Rapid</a></b> (Class I, Mile 1.0)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>5th rapid</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaPhotoDetailView107' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/879887/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/879887.jpg">
</a>
<i>5th rapid</i></div><div>Photo of Bill Cross in canoe by Paul Martzen taken 10/02/11 @ 850 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>One of many easy but busy rapids in this reach.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView62' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101804">Shady Rapid</a></b> (Class I, Mile 1.4)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Shady rapid</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaPhotoDetailView111' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/879888/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/879888.jpg">
</a>
<i>Shady rapid</i></div><div>Photo of Wanda Center by Paul Martzen taken 10/02/11 @ 850 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>The river pushes up against the right bank and forms waves underneath these trees.&nbsp; We managed to get a bit of surfing on the waves.</p><br/><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView63' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101805">Approaching 299 Bridge</a></b> (Class I, Mile 2.9)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Approaching Highway 299 bridge</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaPhotoDetailView115' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/879890/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/879890.jpg">
</a>
<i>Approaching Highway 299 bridge</i></div><div>Photo of Megan Hooker by Paul Martzen taken 10/02/11 @ 850 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>A wide left turn with multiple channels past islands, leads to a right turn and this view of the bridge.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaRiverRapidView64' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid101806">Take Out</a></b> (Class N/A, Mile 3.0)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Take Out at 299</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaPhotoDetailView119' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/879891/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/879891.jpg">
</a>
<i>Take Out at 299</i></div><div>Photo by Paul Martzen taken 10/02/11 @ 850 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>Pull out under the river right side of the bridge.&nbsp; A bridge support with entertaining graffiti blocks the take out and I found the water deeper on the downstream side (at 800 cfs).&nbsp; A gravel road / boat ramp comes right to the water. &nbsp;</p><p>This take out is regularly used by fishermen using rafts and maybe dories.&nbsp;&nbsp; There is plenty of parking and a big turn around circle.</p><br>
<br clear=right>
</div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaCommentGadget66' class='CCommentGadget-view CCommentGadget'><div id='zzqjdq9dlm9gomaCommentGadget66-1'><p> No Comments </p>Users can submit comments.</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
